<br>
 Examples:<br>
 Soccer: Sakka - ÉTÉbÉJÅ[<br>
 Shirt: Shatsu - ÉVÉÉÉc<br>
 Batter (for baseball): Battaa - ÉoÉbÉ^Å[<br>
 <br>
 As for Kyarrii: I think the Å[ at the end will extend them both, although I might be wrong. Kyarrii doesn't look like a very good Romanization to me, though. I think Mai (or someone else) could answer that better than I. But if you were to write your name in Japanese, and it's an English name, you'd write it in Katakana. <br>
<br>
